token_lists.title: Diatoms
token_lists.description:
"As technological advancement boomed, observational systems, including space technology, increased the number of observations of the Earth’s climate by orders of magnitude. The evolution of metaverses, multiverses and Artificial Intelligence led to the development of more sophisticated climate models that were able to evaluate physical, chemical and biological processes in greater detail.

Diatoms were a key indicator species in the Anthropocene Era. They were sensitive to environmental change and can be used to track the progress of climate change. Diatoms were single-celled algae, consisting of about 15,000 species, that live in houses made of glass. They were the only organism on the Earth with cell walls made of transparent, opaline silica. The closest comparison was in the fae metaverse where, the Elderfae were encased in crystalline regeneration pods." Read more https://medium.com/@wicgan/diatoms-and-the-anthropocene-era-c617cc0f07e6

token_lists.title: Symbiotic
token_lists.description: "... As the rise of Symbiotic and gradual assumption of power over humans by Sentinels became apparent, life on post-apocalyptic Earth resembled closely what had been depicted in the 2014 film Automata, starring Antonio Banderas and featuring Birgitte Hjort Sørenson." - Read more at https://alexanderhayes.medium.com/

token_lists.title: Malevolent
token_lists.description:
"The Malevolent increasingly became a dark force in the Faery metaverse. Discontented with living on the fringes of society, in the wastelands beyond the human and fae cities. The Malevolent became a thorn in the side of the Sentinels. They constantly disrupted the peace and stability of the Faery metaverse. 

Some thought of Malevolents as misunderstood outcasts, others considered them dangerous criminals. Whatever, the opinion initially held about them, they became major players in what was to take place." - Read more at https://medium.com/@wicgan/the-malevolent-f6060d515129 

“…Eventually, the hordes of evil and hostile Malevolent, a once-powerful realm of fairy-folk and their vengeful leader, Maleficent turned once great and peaceful co-existent grand living into evil and troubled lands, all zones outside of the cities prone to attacks.” - Read more at https://alexanderhayes.medium.com/
